\begin_layout Standard
As we the focus on studying the expectation of asset ownership and expensive
 non-durable consumption for the purpose of gaining status in the society,
 we are cautious of the extension of some of these ideas on conspicuous
 consumption in the developing world.
 While there is a wealth of literature that finds status competitions to
